{{ill|Sumiyoshi Shrine (Iki City)|lt=Sumiyoshi Shrine|simple||ja|5=住吉神社 (壱岐市)}} is a [[Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located on [[Iki Island]] in [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sumiyoshi Shrine |url=https://www.discover-nagasaki.com/en/sightseeing/100115 |access-date=2023-11-25 |website=【公式】長崎観光/旅行ポータルサイト ながさき旅ネット |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Wondertips |date=2019-08-10 |title=8 Japanese Shinto Shrines that enchant visitors on Iki Island |url=https://wonder-tips.com/2019/08/10/shinto-shrines-ikiisland/ |access-date=2023-11-25 |website=Wondertips |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Iki City Tourism Federation Website |url=http://www.ikikankou.com/english/ |access-date=2023-11-25 |website=Iki City Tourism Federation Website |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Iki City Tourism Federation Website |url=http://www.ikikankou.com/ |access-date=2023-11-25 |website=Iki City Tourism Federation Website |language=ja}}</ref> It is a [[Beppyo shrine]], or a shrine that is particularly notable in a certain way with a significant history to it.<ref>{{Cite web |title=別表神社とは？御朱印めぐりに参考になる「別表神社一覧」とマップ {{!}} 開運戦隊ゴシュインジャー |url=https://jinja-gosyuin.com/beppyou/ |access-date=2023-04-02 |website=jinja-gosyuin.com}}</ref>

It is a Myojon Taisha in the Enhishiki<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QmdRAAAAYAAJ&newbks=0&printsec=frontcover&dq=Sumiyoshi+Shrine+Iki+Island&q=Sumiyoshi+Shrine+Iki+Island&hl=en |title=Engi-shiki; Procedures of the Engi Era: Books VI-X |date=1972 |publisher=Sophia University |language=en}}</ref>

It is a branch shrine of [[Sumiyoshi-taisha]]

